  "Cyanide blocks Complex IV, preventing electron transfer to Oâ‚‚. Since no electrons can exit the chain, all upstream carriers (NADH, FADHâ‚‚, ubiquinone, cytochromes) remain reduced, the proton gradient dissipates, and ATP synthase stops. The Krebs cycle also stalls because NADâپ؛ and FAD cannot be regenerated. Cells are forced to rely on glycolysis alone (2 ATP), which is insufficient for most tissues, especially the brain.": "",
  "A researcher adds 2,4-dinitrophenol (DNP), a chemical uncoupler, to isolated mitochondria. DNP makes the inner mitochondrial membrane permeable to Hâپ؛ ions. What effect does this have on ATP production and oxygen consumption?": "",
