  "ATP production increases because more hydrogen ions are available to drive the ATP synthase complex": "",
  "Both ATP production and oxygen consumption stop completely because the entire ETC shuts down immediately": "",
  "DNP allows Hâپ؛ to leak back across the inner membrane, bypassing ATP synthase. Without the back-pressure of the proton gradient, the ETC runs faster (increasing Oâ‚‚ consumption), but the energy is dissipated as heat rather than used to make ATP. This 'uncoupling' was historically exploited as a dangerous weight-loss drug because it increases metabolic rate and heat production.": "",
