  "Clostridium botulinum is an obligate anaerobe that dies when exposed to atmospheric oxygen. Why is oxygen lethal to this bacterium?": "",
  "It lacks the enzymes (catalase, superoxide dismutase) needed to neutralize toxic reactive oxygen species, so Oâ‚‚ exposure causes fatal oxidative damage to its cellular components": "",
